The World Trade Center Memorial Foundation has garnered support from all living former US presidents, including Bush and Clinton.
Pataki emphasized the importance of the memorial at a New York luncheon.
The project aims to honor the 9/11 victims and raise $500 million for construction.
Notable figures like De Niro and Rockefeller are involved in fundraising efforts.
The memorial will feature pools symbolizing the void left by the twin towers.
Architects detailed plans for the memorial, incorporating remnants of the original towers.
The goal is to create a lasting tribute that educates future generations about the tragedy.
